portunities on the fringes of the health care system, such as cash-only hea=
lth services that don&#8217;t require insurance or tests and apps that aren=
&#8217;t regulated by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration.</em></p></bloc=
kquote><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 1em 0;">It&#8217;s easier to focus on consumers who are able to pay=
 out of pocket and deliver unregulated point solutions. That approach is si=
